<!-- Node: "Single Player Mapping Design Tips." -->
<div class="body_box_header">Single Player Mapping Design Tips.</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2198" title="View user profile.">Andy</a> on Monday, September 6, 2004 - 17:05</small><br /><br />
<!-- by Andy Sep 2004 for Kol: -->
<p>The author of this article, <b>Gary 'Kol' Brigadir</b>, worked with the Issues team and continues to produce maps for Half-Life that are inspiring. Coil is his latest project.</p>
<p> These Tips & Tricks come from reading all there is to read and testing and re-testing theories.  (<i>As well as having actually released something into the public domain :-)</i></p>
<p>There are already a few tutorials here at RUST that look at good design and this is not meant to replace that information, but to enhance it.</p>
To view the whole article, check out:<br><br>
<center><a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/606"><b>Single Player Mapping Design Tips</b></a></center>
