<!-- Node: "Prefabs.Gamedesign.Net Back Online" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Prefabs.Gamedesign.Net Back Online</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">G.A.R.D.</a> on Wednesday, August 25, 2004 - 00:08</small><br /><br />
<center>
<img src="content/news/04_AUG_25/Garg.gif" width="125">
<img src="content/news/04_AUG_25/Crate.gif" width="125">
<img src="content/news/04_AUG_25/star1.gif" width="125">
</center><br>

<b>Great news:</b> Marvin Malkowski Jr has fixed and restarted the upload section of the Rust (Gamedesign.net) <a href="http://prefabs.gamedesign.net/">Prefabs</a> web site.<br><br>

<center>
<img src="content/news/04_AUG_25/Cargo.gif" width="125">
<img src="content/news/04_AUG_25/Trash.gif" width="125">
<img src="content/news/04_AUG_25/Secret2.gif" width="125">
</center><br>

This means the RUST online repository for prefabs is back online with over 2300 prefabs for you to download and try in your maps or upload your prefabs and share with the gamining community!
