<!-- Node: "It is raining in Quake 2 ..." -->
<div class="body_box_header">It is raining in Quake 2 ...</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2" title="View user profile.">G.A.R.D.</a> on Sunday, August 22, 2004 - 00:58</small><br /><br />
<center>
<img border="0" width="250" src="content/quake2/tutorials/make_rain/koldtut8.jpg"><br>
<b>Rain in Quake 2</b><br>
</center><br>

<p>Chris "Kold" Stringer, has just submitted a new tutorial Quake 2 Tutorial on <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/561">making rain</a>. Chris said:</p>

<blockquote>"<i> ... <a href="http://www.planetquake.com/j-spot/jbuzz.html">Jester</a>, a fellow mapper recently made this deathmatch map and despite the amazing brush & texture work .. one thing that caught my attention was the rain, now although Quake2 doesn't support such a feature without a engine mod, there is several way's to make it with one of them being animated (or flowing) textures if you will ... "</i></blockquote>

<p>Check out Kold's Tutorial on <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/561">making rain</a>
<br /><div align=right>
<a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/562#comment" title="Jump to the first comment of this posting.">16 comments</a> &middot; <a href="http://assets.aq2world.com/archive/websites/www.gamedesign.net/node/view/562" title="Read the rest of this posting." class="read-more"><b>Read more</b></a> &middot; 203 reads</div>
</div></td></table><br />
