<!-- Node: "Half-Life Skies" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Half-Life Skies</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/2198" title="View user profile.">Andy</a> on Saturday, August 21, 2004 - 19:55</small><br /><br />
A long overdue guide to <b><a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/558"> Half-Life Skies</a></b> provides information on sky textures, where to find them, how to use them and a short guide on the requirements for making your own.<br><br>

<center>
    <img border="1" width="350" src="content/half-life/tutorials/hlskies/cliff.jpg"><br>
<b>Sample sky texture, as viewed from a cliff</b>
</center><br><br>

It is a graphical tutorial, so those of you that are technologically challenged (like me) might suffer slow download speeds. If you want to know more check out <b><a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/book/view/558"> Half-Life Skies</a></b>
